13) install windows virtual machine
	instructions:
		https://itsfoss.com/install-windows-10-virtualbox-linux/
		there might be problem with secure boot: 
			https://superuser.com/questions/1438279/how-to-sign-a-kernel-module-ubuntu-18-04
		I also used these instructions but I don't think they are needed
			https://stegard.net/2016/10/virtualbox-secure-boot-ubuntu-fail/

	$ sudo apt install virtualbox -> password: funsudus (regular)
	$ sudo reboot

	after following the manual to create a dynamical virtual machine (4GB ram, 200GB ssd, I think this can be changed later), 	
	I opened the VM and loggined into my microsoft account. 

	I noticed I cant drag and drop in between discovered I had to install "windows guest additions"
	This can be done automatically by going through the first two lines in section 4.2.1.1 in the link below (Devices->Insert Guest Addition CD Image...)
	https://docs.oracle.com/en/virtualization/virtualbox/6.0/user/guestossupport.html -> Guest Additions
	This is also a good video on the subject:  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yrqy0Q_zhzI&ab_channel=TechMeSpot
	Windows now had drivers install, it was much faster, and I could copy text from ubuntu host to windows guest.. but file dropping was still a problem for some reason.
	
	I also wanted to know how to do file sharing between the ubuntu host and windows guest
	These are good links to look at: https://helpdeskgeek.com/virtualization/virtualbox-share-folder-host-guest/ AND https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FYmck1G0fqY&ab_channel=TheHowToGuy123

	One last thing.. "sending the shut down signal" didn't do anything. I had to go to the power options in the guest windows and change what pressing the power button does:
	https://forums.virtualbox.org/viewtopic.php?f=8&t=98084

		
