22) install virtualenvwrapper

	guide: https://medium.com/@aaditya.chhabra/virtualenv-with-virtualenvwrapper-on-ubuntu-34850ab9e765
	
	$ sudo apt update
	$ mkdir ~/.virtualenvs
	$ sudo apt install virtualenvwrapper
	$ export WORKON_HOME=~/.virtualenvs -> 
	add "./usr/local/bin/virtualenvwrapper.sh" to ~./bashrc - This was wrong in my case..
	INSTEAD: $ echo "source /usr/share/virtualenvwrapper/virtualenvwrapper.sh" >> ~/.bashrc

	-> type $ virtualenvwrapper to view commands 

	creating a venv in a "project" using virtualenvwrapper: having a "project" will cd to the correct dir when using the "workon" command
	$ export PROJECT_HOME=$(pwd) #assuming terminal is in the project's dir
	$ mkproject -p /usr/bin/python3.9 PythonRobotics #python3.9 is an example, here "PythonRobotics" is the venv's name
	# if the project's path was not as you intended, you can use $ setvirtualenvproject while working on the project and inside the correct dir
	$ deactivate
	$ cd ..
	$ workon PythonRobotics
	$ pip install -r requirements.txt
	#turns out that to view stuff in matplotlib I also need some graphics
	$ pip3 install PyQt5


