37) add apps to right click nautilus-actions.
	#in 20.04: 
		$ sudo apt update
		$ sudo apt -y install nautilus-actions
		$ nautilus -q #restart nautilus after adding stuff 
		# in program, go to edit->perferences-> runtime preferences, remove both V from both boxes in nautilus-menu-layout (nicer look)

	https://ubuntuhandbook.org/index.php/2019/01/install-nautilus-actions-ubuntu-18-04/
	https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=b2HAko2t__E&ab_channel=AJReissig
	
	$ sudo add-apt-repository ppa:daniel-marynicz/filemanager-actions #PPA is a personal package archive
	$ sudo apt update #need to update so it knows about the add PPA
	$ sudo apt install filemanager-actions-nautilus-extension

	the program is called filemanager-actions and can be found through the "show applications"
	can also be opned with $ fma-config-tool

	Note about PPAs: from https://itsfoss.com/how-to-remove-or-delete-ppas-quick-tip/
	'''
	in the effort to install various applications in Ubuntu or other Linux distribution, you often end up adding several PPA.

	Over the time these PPAs might not be updated with the latest version of the operating system. This might create trouble when you try 		updating Ubuntu. You may end up with “Repository does not have a release file” error.

	You may have other reasons as well for deleting or removing a PPA from your system. Whatever be your reason, let me show you how to 		remove a PPA from your system.

	Note: You should uninstall the application in Ubuntu which was installed by the PPA before removing the PPA itself. You can use the ‘apt 		remove’ command for that.
	'''

