52) Install Matlab
	b. download from the website - https://www.mathworks.com/downloads/web_downloads/
	a. unzip
	c. install (I installed on $HOME/LocalInstalls/MATLAB/2021b)
		https://www.mathworks.com/matlabccmake ..entral/answers/518584-how-do-i-install-on-ubuntu
	d. create symbolic link to bin so you can activate matlab from the command
		https://www.mathworks.com/matlabcentral/answers/363731-create-symbolic-links-to-matlab-scripts-and-launcher-and-desktop-shortcut
		$ sudo ln -s $HOME/LocalInstalls/MATLAB/2021b/bin/matlab /usr/local/bin/matlab
	e. to have a matlab icon in favorites tab: https://www.mathworks.com/matlabcentral/answers/20-how-do-i-make-a-desktop-launcher-for-matlab-in-linux		$ sudo apt install matlab-support
		
	f. to enable keyboard shortcuts go to Matlab's preferences (under home tab)->  keyboard -> shortcuts -> change "Emacs" to "Windows"
	https://www.mathworks.com/matlabcentral/answers/103161-why-am-i-unable-to-use-copy-ctrl-c-and-paste-ctrl-v-keyboard-short-cuts-in-the-text-editing-mode

	note: this link also has a cool trick to create a gnome launcher icon to any app installed:	
			'''
			1. Create a linux .desktop file
			$ touch ~/.local/share/applications/matlab.desktop
			2. Add/copy relevant details for app launcher
			[Desktop Entry]
			Version=1.0
			Type=Application
			Terminal=false
			Exec=/path/to/matlab -desktop
			Name=MATLAB RXXXXx
			Icon=/path/to/icon
			Comment=MATLAB
			where /path/to/matlab is recommended to use usr/local/MATLAB/RXXXXx/bin/glnxa64/MATLAB and /path/to/icon is usr/local/MATLAB/RXXXXx/bin/glnxa64/cef_resources/matlab_icon.png
			3. Make the file executable
			$ chmod +x ~/.local/share/applications/matlab.desktop
			4. Test the application launcher from the menu
			From here, I had issues with the icons/descriptions to show. To fix this, I did
			5. Move matlab.desktop to the shared applications folder
			$ sudo mv ~/.local/share/applications/matlab.desktop /usr/share/applications
			$ sudo is required since the root folder is protected
			'''

	note: after running "$ matlab" I have had this message in the terminal: 
		'Gtk-Message: 13:21:42.864: Failed to load module "canberra-gtk-module"'

	I had a problem on my second installation (01/02/2022).
	MATLAB was loading up slow, and when loaded an error would show:
	"java.io.FileNotFoundException: /home/<user>/.matlab/R2021b/History.xml (Permission denied)"
	solved with  this: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/28934046/matlab-error-when-opening-an-error-was-encountered-while-saving-the-command-his
	$ sudo chmod -R 777 .matlab (in home directory) (DONT DO THIS)
		-----> This may be really unadvisable:
			https://www.google.com/search?q=chmod+-R+777&oq=chmod+-R+777&aqs=chrome..69i57.3282j0j4&sourceid=chrome&ie=UTF-8
				#just unadviseable for servers... this is a private system. meh
	to be safer I did this: $ sudo chown -R $LOGNAME: ~/.matlab
	
	I have a second warnning when opening matlab: "Warning: X does not support locale en_IL"
	This was just a language thing I fixed by changing ubuntu settings. 
	figured from here: https://ubuntuforums.org/showthread.php?t=1911860



53) Installing xelatex on ubuntu to convert .ipynb to PDFS
