	#from https://stackoverflow.com/questions/29156653/ipython-jupyter-problems-saving-notebook-as-pdf
	$ sudo apt-get install texlive texlive-latex-extra pandoc texlive-generic-extra texlive-xetex

	AND

	pip install nbconvert[webpdf]

	AND (at least for first time)

	$ jupyter nbconvert --execute --to pdf notebook.ipynb --allow-chromium-download

54) using microsoft word through microsoft edge in ubnutu
	https://www.omgubuntu.co.uk/2021/01/how-to-install-edge-on-ubuntu-linux

	curl https://packages.microsoft.com/keys/microsoft.asc | gpg --dearmor > microsoft.gpg
	sudo install -o root -g root -m 644 microsoft.gpg /etc/apt/trusted.gpg.d/
	sudo sh -c 'echo "deb [arch=amd64] https://packages.microsoft.com/repos/edge stable main" 		> /etc/apt/sources.list.d/microsoft-edge-dev.list'
	sudo rm microsoft.gpg

	follow this to install windows word as an app:
	(basically takes the online version and hooks up to it)
	https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1MvXOx8R0jg&ab_channel=InfinitelyGalactic

	I decided not to work this way because it only works with files online.. not in the comnputer

55) Download Arduino IDE

	$ cd ~/Downloads
